Dropping features¶

In [5]:
Our_data = data.loc[(data.createdOn >= "2015-01-01" )]
print("The shape of data after 01-01-2015 = {}\n".format(Our_data.shape))

#Dropping variables that relate to feScore
drop_main_list = ["barrels08", "barrelsA08", "city08", "city08U" , "cityA08" , "cityA08U" ,"cityCD"
                  , "cityUF" , "co2" , "co2A" , "co2TailpipeAGpm" , "co2TailpipeGpm" , "comb08" ,
                  "comb08U" ,"combA08" , "combA08U" , "combinedCD" , "combinedUF" ,"engId" , 
                  "ghgScore" , "ghgScoreA" , "guzzler", "highway08" , "highway08U" , "highwayA08" ,
                  "highwayA08U" ,"highwayCD" , "highwayUF" , "mpgData" , "rangeA" , "rangeCityA" , 
                  "rangeHwyA" , "UCity" , "UCityA" , "UHighway", "UHighwayA" , "VClass" ,
                  "phevCity" , "phevHwy" , "phevComb" ]

#removing categorical features with high number of levels
drop_list_2 = ['eng_dscr',"trans_dscr" ,'tCharger' , 'sCharger' , "c240Dscr" , "c240bDscr" , 'evMotor']

Our_data = Our_data.drop(drop_main_list , axis=1)
print("The shape of data after 01-01-2015 after dropping variables = {}\n\n".format(Our_data.shape))

Our_data = Our_data.drop(drop_list_2 , axis=1)
print("The shape of data after 01-01-2015 after dropping variables again = {}\n\n".format(Our_data.shape))

#Dropping columns where missing value is greater than 50% 
cols = Our_data.columns.tolist()
for i in range(0, len(cols)):
    col = cols[i]
    if Our_data[col].isnull().sum()*100/len(Our_data) >= 50:
        missing = Our_data[col].isnull().sum()*100/len(Our_data)
        print("Dropping {} because missing perecentage = {:.2f} \n\n".format(col, missing))
        Our_data.drop(col, inplace = True, axis = 1)
        
print("The shape of data after 01-01-2015 after dropping variables with high missing values = {}\n\n".format(Our_data.shape))

# Converting year variable to string 
Our_data["year"]= Our_data["year"].astype(str)

# Splitting columns depending on data type 
cols = Our_data.columns.tolist()
str_column = []
int_column = []
flt_column = []
bool_column =[]
date_column =[]
for col in cols:
    if Our_data[col].dtype == "O":
        str_column.append(col)
    if Our_data[col].dtype == "float64":
        flt_column.append(col)
    if Our_data[col].dtype == "int64":
        int_column.append(col)
    if Our_data[col].dtype == "bool":
        bool_column.append(col)
    if Our_data[col].dtype == "datetime64[ns]":
        date_column.append(col)

print("The number of categorical variables= {}".format(len(str_column)))
print("The number of float variables= {}".format(len(flt_column)))
print("The number of integer type variables= {}".format(len(int_column)))
print("The number of boolean type variables= {}".format(len(bool_column)))
print("The number of date type variables= {}".format(len(date_column)))

Looking at month on month number of datapoints¶

In [7]:
# Looking at month-on-month entry count in the dataset 
Our_data['month'] = Our_data['createdOn'].dt.to_period('M')
mom = pd.DataFrame(Our_data.groupby(["month"])["charge120"].count())
mom = mom.reset_index()

# plotting the number of datapoints in each month
x = np.arange(0,len(mom),1)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1)
fig.set_size_inches(10.5, 6.5)
ax.plot(x,mom['charge120'])
ax.set_xticks(x)
ax.set_xticklabels(mom['month'], rotation='vertical')
ax.set_title("Month on month count of data points")
ax.set_xlabel("Month")
ax.set_ylabel("Number of data points")
plt.show()

We can see a pattern in the number of datapoints reported each month. Highest number of data is received during the months of July-August, while lowest is received during Jan-Feb.

        missing_cols_test.append(col)

# Concatonating training and test datasets for creating dummies
X_train_imputed["test-train"] = "train"
X_test_imputed["test-train"] = "test"
X_2018_imputed["test-train"] = "2018"

frames_2 = [X_train_imputed , X_test_imputed , X_2018_imputed]
total_data_dummy = pd.concat(frames_2)

# Dropping pre decided variables 
total_data_dummy.drop(redundant_cols, inplace = True, axis = 1)
total_data_dummy.drop(new_discard_list, inplace = True, axis = 1)


# creating summy variables
total_data_dummy.phevBlended= (total_data_dummy.phevBlended)*1
total_data_dummy['startStop'] = total_data_dummy['startStop'].map({'N': 0, 'Y': 1})

total_data_dummy["createdOn_date"]= total_data_dummy.createdOn.dt.day
total_data_dummy["createdOn_month"] =total_data_dummy.createdOn.dt.month
total_data_dummy["createdOn_year"]= total_data_dummy.createdOn.dt.year

total_data_dummy["modifiedOn_date"]= total_data_dummy.modifiedOn.dt.day
total_data_dummy["modifiedOn_month"]= total_data_dummy.modifiedOn.dt.month
total_data_dummy["modifiedOn_year"]= total_data_dummy.modifiedOn.dt.year

categorical_features = pd.get_dummies(total_data_dummy[['createdOn_date','createdOn_month','createdOn_year',
                                                          'modifiedOn_date','modifiedOn_month','modifiedOn_year']])

total_data_dummy = pd.concat([total_data_dummy,categorical_features],axis=1)

#dropping features for which dummies were created
total_data_dummy.drop(["createdOn", "modifiedOn",'createdOn_date','createdOn_month','createdOn_year','modifiedOn_date','modifiedOn_month','modifiedOn_year'], inplace = True, axis = 1)

#str_column.remove("month")
object_features = pd.get_dummies(total_data_dummy[str_column])
total_data_dummy = pd.concat([total_data_dummy,object_features],axis=1)

#dropping features for which dummies were created
total_data_dummy.drop(str_column, inplace = True, axis = 1)

X_train_dummy = total_data_dummy[total_data_dummy["test-train"] == "train"]
X_test_dummy = total_data_dummy[total_data_dummy["test-train"] == "test"]
X_2018_dummy = total_data_dummy[total_data_dummy["test-train"] == "2018"]

X_train_dummy.drop("test-train", inplace = True, axis = 1)
X_test_dummy.drop("test-train", inplace = True, axis = 1)
X_2018_dummy.drop("test-train", inplace = True, axis = 1)


print("The shape of training data after creating dummy variables = {}\n".format(X_train_dummy.shape))
print("The shape of test data after creating dummy variables = {}\n".format(X_test_dummy.shape))
print("The shape of 2018 data after creating dummy variables = {}\n".format(X_2018_dummy.shape))

The shape of training data after creating dummy variables = (2665, 1343)

The shape of test data after creating dummy variables = (1143, 1343)

The shape of 2018 data after creating dummy variables = (91, 1343)

      % mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_gbr_feat))
# Explained variance score: 1 is perfect prediction
print('Variance score using GBR with feature selection: %.2f' % r2_score(y_test, y_pred_gbr_feat))
